  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The development shall be carried out in accordance with the reports, specifications and drawings detailed Existing Front Elevation (received 22/07/2022), Location Plan (received 22/07/2022), signage details document (received 23/08/2022).  \r\nReason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development and to allow the local planning authority to review any potential changes to the scheme. \r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The maximum steady brightness of the fascia sign hereby permitted is not to exceed 600 candelas per sq.m.\r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy DMS8 and to comply with paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - The maximum steady brightness of the projecting sign hereby permitted is not to exceed 600 candelas per sq.m. \r\nReason: To ensure the proposed sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) and to comply with paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - The illumination of the sign(s) hereby permitted shall be by static illumination only. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with Council policy DMS8 and to comply with paragraph 132 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.\r\n"
